    "summary": "Reassessment of 15 previously known high-velocity stars (11 HVS candidates: HVS 1,3,4,5,6,7,8,9,10,12,13 plus 4 RV outliers: B434,B485,B711,B733) using Gaia DR2 proper motions and revised spectrophotometric distances from Irrgang+2018 (Paper I). Monte Carlo orbit integration in 3 MW mass models (Irrgang+2013). Under Model I (baseline): 5 stars confirmed unbound (HVS 3,5,7,8,12) with non-GC disk origin; 6 stars unbound but astrometry insufficient to constrain origin (HVS 1,4,6,9,10,13); 4 stars bound disk runaways (B434,B485,B711,B733). Ejection velocities for 5 non-GC stars near or above BSE/DE limits, suggesting additional powerful ejection mechanism. HVS 3 confirmed LMC origin with v_ej=870 km/s. Paper provides Table 1 (input kinematics) and appendix tables with full kinematic parameters."
